== Technique 10: Heat as Insurance (When in Doubt, Cook It Through)

=== The Concept

If you're ever uncertain about the safety or quality of scraps—they've been sitting a bit too long, they smell borderline, you're not sure if they were contaminated—_cook them through_.

Heat is the great sanitizer. Cooking scraps to 165°F (74°C) will kill most pathogens. This doesn't fix rotten or moldy food (if it's bad, throw it out), but it does provide a safety margin for borderline items.

=== Applications

- _Frittatas:_ Eggs + scraps, cooked through in a skillet or oven.
- _Soups:_ Boil scraps in stock for 20+ minutes.
- _Stir-fries:_ High heat + constant motion = thorough cooking.
- _Baked dishes:_ Gratins, casseroles, savory bread puddings.

